description: GetTile returns a tile. Map tiles are used by clients to render a map. they're addressed using a grid arrangement with an X coordinate, Y coordinate, and Z (zoom) level.

parameters.name: Tileset
parameters.description: Specifies the desired tile set. Valid Values: raster.satellite | vector.basemap.

parameters.name: Z
parameters.description: The zoom value for the map tile.

parameters.name: X
parameters.description: The X axis value for the map tile. Must be between 0 and 19.

parameters.name: Y
parameters.description: The Y axis value for the map tile.

nested_items.name: Blob
nested_items.description: The blob represents a vector tile in mvt or a raster tile in an image format.

nested_items.name: ContentType
nested_items.description: Header that represents the format of the response. The response returns the following as the HTTP body.

nested_items.name: CacheControl
nested_items.description: Header that instructs caching configuration for the client.

nested_items.name: ETag
nested_items.description: The pricing bucket for which the request is charged at.

nested_items.name: PricingBucket
nested_items.description: The pricing bucket for which the request is charged at.
